<Review>I really like the brunch they have at Marengo.  First off, the mimosas and bloody mary's are terrific here. The food is well made and service has always been friendly and fun.  The back room has big skylights and opens up so is a lot of fun on a sunny day (while still inside).  Marengo will get crowded, especially on a nice weekend so its good to get there earlier for brunch.  The back bar will also fill up but it is always a fun time.</Review>< Pics>

<Review>Eye candy is usually pretty promising and making out with strangers is not so irregular here. While, it's a great spot to socialize it's my go to for Einst√∂k beer when feeling nostalgic for Iceland. Their salads are great and the loaded queso is fire! The chicken jerk salad is spicy and hearty. The small salads are still massive for one person. The large is big enough to split with a friend. Sliders are delicious and big selection to pick from. It's a must for visitors from the other side of the pound so they can try a chicken waffle slider. I promise they're going to be excited because this combo is just bizarre to anyone other than Americans.< /Review></record></dataset><record>

< text>
The Hollywood Pad Thai dish was so delicious, moist, and sweet; you will not be able to stop eating it!  I ordered the Glass Noodle dish at a medium heat level, but it was too spicy for me. The broth in the glass Noodle was comfort food nirvana. The Panang curry was coconut heaven. The Glass Noodle dish didn't have much protein, so order more if your expecting more protein ratios. Overall, a delightful neighborhood family business that I will visit again and again.</text>

116728095651270953775< /userid>
<username>Alex P<//username><date>1559446915688</date>< Rating>
5</Rating>
< text>
This is surprisingly one of the best Thai food place I know of. It's one of the hole in a wall that most people don't seem to know . Their food is less Americanized than let's say president Thai. Here are few item we tried :
-Crispy pork with Chinese broccoli. Definitely better than many other place where the pork is too hard. In alot of the places my jaw will be tired from chewing the pork and this place has done it right where it's actually crispy , not hard.
-Chicken pad Thai : good portion and not too sweet with a good flavor . Nothing too special here but still definitely good.
- beef Penang. I only tried a little bit of this one since I can't really eat spicy , but my party members definitely impressed by it as it's not too sweet and has a really nice spices scent .

Price is reasonable where the three dishes I mentioned cost me $35 after tax on June 2019.
So average food was about $10 which is really reasonable in these day.

Place is kinda hard to find since they don't have good signage . I've been here before and still wasn't sure if this place has changed name or not since I can't see the restaurant name from the street when you drive by it.</text>

She rang me up and handed me a empty coffee mug. I told her I want the OJ in a glass. She apologized and got me a glass.
I went outside to find a table.
There were 7 or 8 tables and I passed 4 before I found one that had been cleaned after the last customers. When the breakfast came it was 2 eggs and 4 bacon.

<text>I felt the need to say something after reading all the negative reviews here lately. I'm a fitness/health nut. I don't eat anything made of flour or starch not because of allergens or disease, but because I simply want to be putting more nutritious things into my body. That said, who doesn't love bread? I found Julian's bakery about 2-3 years ago, and they are the only reason I have bread in my life to this day. I've tried probably all of their variations, and they're all winners to me. I'm not a picky person when it comes to taste, I understand there's a slight sacrifice you make when choosing health food alternatives, but considering the nutritional profile of these breads, I think they're AMAZING. I could not be more grateful that this company exists. Some of their breads are a bit better than others (the paleos tend to go bad super fast and sometimes taste odd), but some are downright delicious. Know what you're buying and don't expect it to taste like a loaf of fresh sourdough, appreciate it for what it is.<//text><pictures>None< /pictures><Resp>None< /Resp>< gmapID>

< Text>
Julian Bakery's has a wide selection of gluten-free and low-carb bread and bakery items. I have celiac disease (gluten intolerance) and my husband has type 1 diabetes (requires low-carb diet) so these products are perfect for us. I was so excited about all the gluten free treats that I bought 2 of every muffin or goody that they had in the store. Unfortunately not much tasted very good. I understand that most of the things I got were basically sugar free, but still, some were just terrible. Some were tolerable. The no-carb bread isn't very good, but if you need a no-carb option for sandwiches it will do. I've had really, really good gluten free bakery items before as well as low-carb bread, so I know it's possible to do in a tasty fashion! I think they need to change their recipes - or from what I've read in other reviews, go back to old recipes. It's cool to see a place trying to make a dent in this very open market, but unfortunately they aren't succeeding.</Text>

<UserId.>110893614992510701273<//UserId.>< user_name>
Robin Whang< /user_name>
<Date>1605400307592</Date><Rate>5< /Rate>< Review>
My wife and I went out for a walk a week ago, checking out the various outdoor dining options around Old Town Pasadena for our anniversary dinner in a few days. After checking out the hustle and bustle of Colorado, we skipped down to Green and as soon as we turned the corner and walked through, we saw this place and immediately smelled the delicious aromas coming from the kitchen. Done!

We sent an email requesting a reservation for Wednesday evening at 630 pm, and arrived 15 minutes early. Being a weeknight, it wasn't terribly busy but a couple other groups showed up within 15 minutes of us being seated as well.

The smells that intrigued us a few days ago had not led us astray - this place was great! The owners and wait staff were very attentive, courteous, and fun. They kept our bread basket full, our souls warm with good cheer, and bellies happily full with the food we ordered. We were particularly smitten with the brie en croute appetizer - warm brie cheese in a puff pastry and savory sauce. Yum!

My wife also thoroughly enjoyed her roast chicken (and what a mound of fries that came with!), while I ordered their pork chop special they had that evening. All so so good. We will definitely be back here again soon!<//Review>

<user_id>118305099099172840156< /user_id>< Review>
My husband and I came here for our wedding anniversary and I have been trying to find a reason to come here since opening. Having a French Bistro restaurant in the Pasadena neighborhood is definitely a plus (we were getting bored of the same type of cuisines). The location is really cute and all I could think about is their dessert.

We had the seafood bouillabaisse and lamb rack. Both were cook perfectly with the right level of seasoning. I am no expert in French food but I thoroughly enjoyed the experience. We also the escargots as an appetizer. The pear dessert though...... gosh, it‚Äôs AMAZINGLY good. I watch a lot of cooking shows and have seen people doing it but tasting it for the first time blown my mind away. The pear dessert is unique to this place in Pasadena and I would recommend skipping all the other dessert and get this. Unless I have been living under the rock (which is partially true), the chocolate pot, cream br√ªl√©e, apple tartine, and creme anglaise are desserts you can get it everywhere else. So get adventurous and get the pear.

The service are also very intimate. The servers are very attentive and the owners were out here speaking to us as well.

Wrapping this up; we lived in Pasadena for quite some time and I am so glad this place opened up. Welcome to the neighborhood! Keep up the good work! We are looking forward to many many delicious French food to come.<//Review>

<review>COVID REVIEW: We've dined in and ordered out with Entre Nous since COVID restaurant restrictions were lifted - each time has resulted in fabulous, attentive, and safe experiences.

FOOD
Per usual, each dish is phenomenal. Try the Tahiti-style mussels! Buttery, garlicy escargots are truly decadent. My favorite is the sea bass over lentils. I love how Entre Nous stays true to their French style without being overly complicated; they use simple ingredients and transform them into luxurious dishes that leave you more than satisfied.

AMBIANCE
Last night, we were able to experience Entre Nous' patio dining experience. They have loads of seating under the lovely trees alongside Green Street. Tables offer the same intimate experience of dining by candlelight while experiencing all the safety protocols during this pandemic. This is the best al fresco dining experience in Old Town Pasadena.

STAFF
Consistently friendly, knowledgeable, helpful, and energetic. You won't find distracted or uncaring personnel here...  As with many small businesses bending with the hurdles of this crisis, all of the staff of Entre Nous are stoic, professional, and manage the stresses I'm sure they're all experiencing. You're truly treated like old friends when you visit!

Please visit Entre Nous!< /review><time>1598209975154</time><rating>5</rating>< pictures>
None</pictures>

<Resp>{'time': 1522691744615, 'text': 'Thanks Adaline for the love!'}< /Resp>< review>
The entire staff here is amazing, and the prices are phenomenally fair! I came in to get my hair coloured and cut, and Kelly did an amazing job. They even offer a free beer when you get a cut, it's pretty neat (shame I don't drink)! Unlike some salons where they're not really on top of what's currently fashionable or trendy, the team here is up-to-date and I left with a wicked good pixie cut.

I am a transgender woman, and no one in the location even batted an eye when I came in, everyone used my correct pronouns and was super respectful. And as someone that is non-binary, I appreciate that their pricing for cuts is based on length and not gender. This is a safe space.

The decor is pretty great, too! I just love the aesthetic. If you need a cut for a great price, want your colour done, or any of the above, come over to Bishops!<//review>

My first time there and went with a friend. Place is a little pricey, $13 talking about splitting a pastrami sandwich but it's a lot of meat and it's very thinly shaved. Unlike the hat and many other restaurants that seem to have good pastrami but just a little on the chewier side this is very thinly sliced and wasn't chewy at all. Probably one of the better pastrami sandwiches I've ever had. Just comes on a simple roll with mustard and pickles. I noticed everybody around me was eating fried zucchini fries as they refer to them which are the thinner zucchini like a french fry that are crispy all the way through not soggy on the inside. I decided to go for onion rings which were good but I've definitely had better. But they were tasty.  Saw they do fries, sweet potato fries, fried mushrooms. They also have a milkshake and ice cream bar ready to make you a Sundae.<//Text>

<Text>It's a great place for small groups. It's also good for just families. We usually order a large sampler (fries, onion rings, fried zucchini, fried mushrooms), which is enough for the four of us and then a burger. Overall a great family dining experience.
1. Portions are very large and satisfying. Though it may seem pricey, each order is large enough for two meals.
2. This is a diner atmosphere so don't expect much more than that. However, the vintage memorabilia add to the ambiance.
3. Staff have always been friendly and helpful.
4. Parking has never been a problem for me, but I haven't been there at peak hours.<//Text><pictures>None< /pictures><response>None<//response>< gmap_id>

<user_name>Jen Es<//user_name><Date>1526249513025<//Date><Rate>5<//Rate>< text>
Today was the 1st time we came to try this place out. I was looking for restaurants in Glendora, where my brother lives (he recently moved there). I found this place on here (I like to read reviews that also has the owner/manager replying back to the reviewer, this tells me that they care & a sign of great customer service üëç) & told my brother to meet us here for lunch.
It was a great place!!! I like all the decor, from classic license plates to photos of Lucille Ball, Audrey Hepburn, Betty Boop & lots & lots of memorabilias that I could just read & look at. This resto felt welcoming, spacious & nostalgic. It reminds you of the fun, good old days, no worries at all.... Oh BTW the food is very good!!! My sons like the chili cheese  burger combo, my brother had the pastrami (pretty good portion of pastrami üëç) & I had the mess burrito. Sooo many to choose from. They also have other condiments, 4 different salsas, huge jalepenos, onions/cilantro (I think that's what it looks like) & pickled small yellow peppers/carrots/onions. When we get a chance to come back I'd like to try the French toast, didn't make it before 11am ‚òπÔ∏è, next time. Overall üëçüëå</text>

<Review>Ever meet someone who is always with whatever is the hot in "thing" but you still dont want to be around them?

Thats kinda what I feel about Legends Classic Diner

Its amazing how you put a bunch of crap on the walls and people get all "jazzed" about a theme.

The real theme of this place is deep fried not that great food.

I have been here more times then I like to recall because it took quite a few times to convince people that this place just isn't good.

I will say that nothing is horrible. Just nothing stands out at all and considering how much fat is in everything and the fact I can bump into a Greek burger place with my eyes closed.

Almost everything deep fried is overcooked and dry. The food is also just bland.

Feel free to come here just dont come crying to me about it.<//Review>< gmap_id>
